WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:13.080
And now Words and Their Stories from VOA Learning English.

2
00:00:19.610 --> 00:00:23.210
Springtime is a time of renewal and growth.

3
00:00:24.770 --> 00:00:30.870
Many plants end their long winter sleep and form new buds and shoots.

4
00:00:32.890 --> 00:00:36.530
Beautiful flowers will soon be showing their bright colors.

5
00:00:37.050 --> 00:00:41.470
And the grass will grow thicker and greener again.

6
00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:49.930
Some flowers bloom in a very noticeable way but that is not the case with grass.

7
00:00:51.290 --> 00:00:54.910
Imagine you are sitting in a grassy field.

8
00:00:55.650 --> 00:01:00.090
And you have only one job - to watch the grass grow.

9
00:01:01.150 --> 00:01:03.810
That does not sound very interesting.

10
00:01:03.810 --> 00:01:07.950
In fact, it sounds really boring.

11
00:01:09.870 --> 00:01:21.270
That idea is what gives us the expression "like watching grass grow." We use this expression to describe an experience that is uninteresting.

12
00:01:22.670 --> 00:01:26.610
Another good word to describe it is tedious.

13
00:01:28.250 --> 00:01:31.690
We use this expression in many situations.

14
00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:44.030
Let's hear a few examples: After the politician won his campaign, he gave a two-hour long acceptance speech.

15
00:01:45.230 --> 00:01:46.150
Two hours!

16
00:01:46.830 --> 00:01:49.970
It was as much fun as watching grass grow.

17
00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:54.690
I really don't like watching long sports games.

18
00:01:54.690 --> 00:01:57.750
It's like watching grass grow.

19
00:01:58.890 --> 00:02:02.130
Now, grass grows on the ground all the time.

20
00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:05.490
And usually, we don't give it much thought.

21
00:02:06.830 --> 00:02:13.410
If you stand in one place for a long time, the grass will continue to grow under your feet.

22
00:02:14.550 --> 00:02:25.190
For people who are always active, always moving, always on-the-go, we can say they don't let grass grow under their feet.

23
00:02:26.550 --> 00:02:28.890
We can also say beneath their feet.

24
00:02:30.630 --> 00:02:34.310
And sometimes we use this expression as a command.

25
00:02:35.790 --> 00:02:41.010
Let's hear some examples: Don't let the grass grow beneath your feet.

26
00:02:41.650 --> 00:02:42.510
Get back to work.

27
00:02:43.710 --> 00:02:47.210
She certainly doesn't let the grass grow under her feet.

28
00:02:47.890 --> 00:02:51.330
She's been traveling non-stop for over a year.

29
00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:56.820
And that's all the time we have for this Words and Their Stories.

30
00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:00.280
Until next time, I'm Anna Matteo.
